# Environment Configuration for Vehicle Order Tracker

# =============================================================================
# PRODUCTION CONFIGURATION (Default)
# =============================================================================
# By default, the application uses Google Cloud Application Default Credentials
# (ADC) for authentication with Vertex AI. This requires:
# 1. A service account with "Vertex AI User" role attached to your Cloud Run service
# 2. No API keys needed in environment variables
#
# When deployed to Cloud Run, the container automatically uses the attached 
# service account credentials. No additional configuration required.

# Optional: Specify Google Cloud project ID (auto-detected if not set)
# GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT=your-project-id

# Optional: Specify Vertex AI location (defaults to us-central1)
# VERTEX_AI_LOCATION=us-central1

# Optional: Specify server port (defaults to 8080)
# PORT=8080

# =============================================================================
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT CONFIGURATION (Optional)
# =============================================================================
# For local development, you have two options:

# Option 1 (Recommended): Use gcloud CLI for authentication
# Run: gcloud auth application-default login
# This creates local credentials that the app will use automatically

# Option 2 (Fallback): Use a local Gemini API key for development only
# Uncomment the line below and add your API key
# Note: This is for local dev only and should NOT be used in production
# LOCAL_GEMINI_KEY=your-gemini-api-key-here

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# =============================================================================
# ⚠️  NEVER commit API keys to version control
# ⚠️  NEVER expose service account key files
# ⚠️  Use .env.local for local secrets (already in .gitignore)
# ✅  Production deployments should use service account IAM roles only
# ✅  Delete unused API keys from Google Cloud Console after migration

# =============================================================================
# FIREBASE CONFIGURATION (if needed)
# =============================================================================
# Firebase configuration is typically embedded in the frontend bundle
# No environment variables needed for Firebase client SDK
